# Load a saved map and start localizing against it (robot-side). `kind`:
#   "2d"   -> start the localization stack (AMCL + map_server) on the 2D map
#   "3d"   -> reload the OctoMap binary tree into the 3D mapping node
#   "both" -> do both (they share the same map frame, so one /initialpose covers both)
# After loading, set the robot's start pose with /initialpose (the GUI publishes
# it from a click-drag on the map).
string name
string kind                  # "2d" | "3d" | "both"
---
bool success
string message
